CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 25, 1963, pg. 2 reads: " Plan Rally - The planning committee for the big NAACP Centennial Rally, to be held Sunday, June 9, from 4 to 6 P.M., in the Civic Arena, is shown as it went over final plans this week. Left to right, around  the table, are Byrd Brown, Mrs. Aldora S. Frazier, Harriette McCray, the Rev. R.C. Eberhardt, the Rev. Herbert Wilkerman, Lorende Tyler, Justin M. Johnson, E. Josephine Martin, Dorothy K. Williams, Fay Adams, Stanton Hammon and Mrs. Sarah Robinson. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, clockwise: Byrd Brown, Aldora Sanders Frazier, Harriette McCray, Rev. R.C. Eberhardt, Rev. Herbert Wilkerman, Lorende Tyler, Justin M. Johnson, E. Josephine Martin, Dorothy K. Williams, Fay Adams, Stanton Hammon, and Sarah Robinson, seated around rectangular table for NAACP Centennial Rally meeting
